{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"d37a4320-5f52-45e9-8e10-c9ca216f4118","agentId":"a490f9b6956c211b9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"\nFeature: Game of Life - Next Generation\nTest file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts\nImplementation file: src/game-of-life.ts\n\nRequirements:\n- Implement Conway's Game of Life with an infinite grid\n- Accept an array of living cells as [x, y] coordinate tuples\n- Return the next generation of living cells\n- Rules:\n  1. Underpopulation: Any live cell with fewer than 2 live neighbors dies\n  2. Survival: Any live cell with 2 or 3 live neighbors lives on\n  3. Overpopulation: Any live cell with more than 3 live neighbors dies\n  4. Reproduction: Any dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive\n- Use sparse representation (only store living cells)\n- Handle negative coordinates\n- Grid is infinite in all directions\n\nAPI contract:\n```ts\ntype Cell = [number, number]; // [x, y]\nexport function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[];\n```\n\nExamples from the spec:\n- Empty grid stays empty\n- Single cell dies (underpopulation)\n- Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation - each has 1 neighbor)\n- Cell with 2 neighbors survives\n- Cell with 3 neighbors survives\n- Cell with 4+ neighbors dies (overpopulation)\n- Dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)\n- Block pattern (still life) - stays the same\n- Blinker pattern (oscillator) - oscillates\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, no HITL checkpoints.\n"},"uuid":"dee382c1-6139-4ed0-a44d-9449bac69eeb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T18:42:57.380Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-14_18-42-22_game-of-life-example-mapping_v4-exact-subagents_opus-4-6-portkey-no-thinking","sessionId":"cd79627f-c0fe-435c-9610-75a50007f2d2","version":"2.1.107","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"lovely-baking-lynx"}
